{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r742139252", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "A fantastic evening and a great waitress! ", "diner_date": " January 2020", "rating_date": "30 January 2020", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "L8553AUwillb", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "2"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r742139252-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["A fantastic evening in the Ivy, made particularly special by the the attentive waitress Amy (Auburn hair). She was attentive, knowledgable and funny, making the whole party feel at ease and welcome in the fantastic setting! Great job, I hope she is recognised for her professional and friendly attitude."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r741794883", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "2", "title": "Not Birthday Celebration Friendly! Beware.", "diner_date": " January 2020", "rating_date": "28 January 2020", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "damhy", "reviewer_origin": ["Bromley, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "12"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "7"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["30", "10", "30"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r741794883-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Having frequented various Ivy restaurants and been very happy with both food and service, I selected this one for a birthday brunch with friends for my wife. This went off to a bad start because, the waitress spotted that I had brought my own birthday cake with me and wanted to take that away to the reception. ", "Following, I asked to speak to a manager about this and had an unfortunate experience talking to Audrius, who I found lacked any kind of human emotion and was frankly facetious and patronising, there was obviously no negotiation on their matter of their \"health and safety policy\" over bringing external cakes, although it was clear from Audrius that the issue was really about the effect it would have on dessert sales. Audrius explained that this happens a lot, and many guest find themselves in my position and allowing any discretion would mean people: \"bringing their own wine or dogs to the restaurant\u201d. This indicates to me, that customers have a desire to do exactly as I had done, and that the restaurant itself is not listening to customers\u2019 desires or needs. Anyway, the discussion ended with him saying \"You have a choice to make?\", when I enquired as to the choice, I was told: \"To sit down and enjoy your meal or not?\", which I thought was unprofessional. If this was my brand I would not have such a person represent it.", "Notwithstanding that the Ivy is not a patisserie, does not specialise in birthday cakes and anything they would have offered would have been far inferior. What is more frustrating is that when I called the restaurant prior to the booking, I was told that they can only provide birthday cakes for up to 5 people, and since there were 8 of us, this was not an option. Although Audrius insisted this was not the case, so not only poor management, but poor staff advice led to this situation occurring.", "Even other restaurant guests who overheard the conversation made the effort to to approach us and offer their supporting voices that this was a ridiculous policy.", "Talking to one of the other managers, Alex, when we left, who I found much more personable, and at least had the trait of human empathy, which honestly is the minimum I would expect from anyone in the hospitality industry. It was nice that someone in the restaurant was able to consider my situation and that of my guests from our perspective.", "Food was less than the Ivy standard I have come to know which was extremely disappointing, especially as I introduced so many people to the Ivy for the first time and talked it up, perhaps it was just this particular restaurant, but I will never come here again, nor would I expect that from my guests who came for the first time. Several of us, commented was lacking in various ways. Unfortunately this occasion did not live up to my high expectations from the Ivy that I've enjoyed at many other locations across London as a regular customer, but the \"Ivy in the Park - Canary Wharf\" has left me burnt and offended.", "I seriously urge a reconsideration on the birthday cake policy, it\u2019s surely a classic managerial short sightedness where you intend to increase revenue by potentially increasing sales of desserts on a single occasion, but neglect that you offend customers and limit future sales when people who\u2019ve enjoyed friendly and accommodating service come back time and time again. Not to mention that even bringing your own cake means that customers would still purchase teas and coffees. Due to the hostility in this restaurant we took the cake and made the celebrations at another local venue who were more than happy to give us a table when we purchased a few drinks to go with it!"]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r747592193", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Monday night team dinner....", "diner_date": " February 2020", "rating_date": "25 February 2020", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "MJ77777777", "reviewer_origin": ["Kent, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "15"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "4"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r747592193-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["All 6 people had a starter and a main course, no deserts. Excellent food all round, no complaints at all.", "For the mains our group had;- Salmon, Black Miso Cod, Fillet Steak, Crab cakes and two Duck curry dishes. For starters we had the tuna carpaccio, scallops, tempura prawns,"]}
