{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r743218816", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Lovely anniversary meal", "diner_date": " January 2020", "rating_date": "5 February 2020", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "julesA1", "reviewer_origin": ["Stafford"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "39"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "9"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["50", "50", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r743218816-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["My husband took me here for a meal as part of our wedding anniversary celebrations. This is a very pleasant environment with a lovely ambiance.I had the Salmon and my husband had the lobster. The food was superb, cooked to perfection. The desserts were good and it was difficult to choose from the fabulous selection. The staff were very attentive, in fact my only criticism would be they were too attentive, making me feel a little rushed. But all in all a good experience and I would definitely dine here again."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r743911955", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "George the waiter enhanced the feel good factor!!", "diner_date": " February 2020", "rating_date": "9 February 2020", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "pfizerhead", "reviewer_origin": ["cork"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "12"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "3"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r743911955-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Has a scrumptious meal to celebrate our friend's special birthday. Great company, great food, great ambiance. Our lovely visit was most definitely enhanced by our funny, friendly, wonderful waiter George, and another equally lovely head waiter whose name we didn't get...photo bomber you know who you are. Will definitely be returning #lovetheIvy"]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r743837109", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "4", "title": "Good food, Amazing service", "diner_date": " February 2020", "rating_date": "9 February 2020", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "FoodieTay0", "reviewer_origin": ["Essex, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "2"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "5"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r743837109-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["We took our mum here for a bday meal. We sat in the conservatory type area which was a bit chilly at some moments despite the hidden heaters under the tables. ", "Food:", "Good sized portions. The lobster risotto starter is delicious, sea bass main was okay (it comes with A LOT of oil). The Sirloin amazing!! BTW Chips portions are real portions :-)", "Service:", "Which is why I\u2019m writing this review. We had Steve as our waiter; he was so lovely and always happy to help answer any questions. I\u2019m a waiters nightmare, not deliberately but I love all food and I\u2019m very indecisive about which option to commit to. Steve was happy to answer my questions and narrow my choices down to one. With my indecisiveness and our mum being on crutches, I sometimes worry that pretentious restaurant staff will put a downer on the evening. This was not the case at The Ivy Canary Wharf and I will definitely be returning again."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r745522441", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Large table for a surprise birthday", "diner_date": " January 2020", "rating_date": "16 February 2020", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Blossomhill1", "reviewer_origin": ["Essex, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "114"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "66"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r745522441-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["We went here to celebrate a friends birthday , fab cocktail bar to start with , a variety of drinks to please all .This place has a garden feel with nooks and crannies ,we were in the conservatory .Lovely atmosphere , cosy and intimate and busy .Comfortable seating arrangements .The food was lovely, a varied menu , we all had different meals and everyone was happy with them . We thought it was very reasonable for London as we had quite a lot of alcohol to drink and went through the card for dinner .The chocolate bomb for dessert is to die for ! .Have no complaints at all with the staff or the service .A word of warning to the ladies with stilettos on , floor a bit slippery under foot ! Only a 3 minute walk from station .....Would love to go back !"]}
