{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r741637025", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Trully great", "diner_date": " January 2020", "rating_date": "27 January 2020", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "wladimircv", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "10"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "2"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["50", "50", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r741637025-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Outstanding service, just had a dinner with my better half. We both had steaks (although mine was a bit of a disappointment) few starters and dessert, everything was perfect. We have been looked after the head waitress and the manager.", "Great vibes, gives you a sort of vintage experience, kind of posh but not too formal.", "Definitely coming back."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r736900704", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Amazing Service and Quality Food!", "diner_date": " December 2019", "rating_date": "4 January 2020", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Sil-ftq", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "4"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "1"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["50", "50", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r736900704-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["I went to The Ivy in The Park for New Year's Eve and I highly recommend it for everyone! Staff is very polite and the restaurant is stunning! Quality-price is good! Steve was our first waiter, who was very friendly and attentive, he recommended some dishes and I can tell the texture and the flavour were super! Valerio took care of us after the mains, he went extra mile to make our experience memorable and recommended an amazing desert!", "I will definitely come back! Thank you!"]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r738527124", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "4", "title": "Nice evening. ", "diner_date": " January 2020", "rating_date": "11 January 2020", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "LoSDiner", "reviewer_origin": ["Leigh-on Sea, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "469"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "271"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r738527124-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Overall I had a really pleasant evening catching up with some friends I had not seen for a while. Overall a nice meal, service was attentive without being obtrusive and the restaurant had a nice feel to it. It was a shame my steak was cooked incorrectly, I asked for medium rare and it was well done. However the mistake was dealt with quickly and efficiently. My companions were all happy with their meals. "]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r739965166", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "3", "title": "Average", "diner_date": " January 2020", "rating_date": "19 January 2020", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "PCDines", "reviewer_origin": ["Greater London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "28"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "12"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["20", "20", "30"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r739965166-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Visited on a Saturday night. Lovely welcome and our initial waitress was pleasant and engaged with us. The food was mostly lovely. The exception was the chips, they were dry, tasteless & oven cooked in our opinion, We ordered wine and our main course was served before it arrived at the table. From this point on the new female server, now in a black suit did not engage with us. Our wine & water were topped up as she passed with out a single glance at us and the bottles replaced on the table with a definite thump. We were not asked if we wanted dessert but the menu was plonked in front of us without comment. We were then left for at least 20 minutes before anyone asked us if we wanted to order. As we wanted some cheese to go with our remaining wine we sat sipping water, once ordered the cheese took ages to arrive to the point that we asked ourselves who had ordered something complicated! The background music was too loud, without any discernible tune and had a constant beat that made it hard to ignore and conversation difficult. On a separate note ladies have to queue in the corridor before they even get onto the Ladies toilets and 3 cubicles for a restaurant of this size is inadequate. For a chain that pitches themselves as luxury we felt that they need to try a lot harder."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r739602301", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "3", "title": "Flashy venue but food not up to scratch ", "diner_date": " January 2020", "rating_date": "17 January 2020", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Matthew S", "reviewer_origin": ["West Byfleet, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "351"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "76"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r739602301-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["The venue is quite attrsctive with a faux art deco theme but is let down by fairly mediocre food, including dry chips and slightly soggy milanese. Like many of the branches of the Ivy, much of the clientele seems to be there in the hope of spotting celebs but no chance of that in Canary Wharf!"]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r741030679", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Great experience", "diner_date": " January 2020", "rating_date": "24 January 2020", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "francescobraun", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "2"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r741030679-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Went for dinner with my girlfriend on a Friday night, quite busy but lovely vibes. Food was good, especially the meat. We had Lobster Risotto as starter, a Steak Tartare and a Rib-eye as mains and a delicious Chocolate Bomb dessert, along with few cocktails from the special menu, both nice.", "Special mention to the staff, in particilar our waiter Adam, incredibly helpful with recommending the courses and with a great sense of hospitality."]}
