{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r733069591", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Great Restuarant", "diner_date": " December 2019", "rating_date": "16 December 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Kbright98", "reviewer_origin": ["Essex, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "9"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "11"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r733069591-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["As we were slightly early we were invited to sit at the bar, and try the cocktails. This was very enjoyable and a great start to the evening. We were seated in the upstairs restaurant and our cocktails were brought up to our table from the downstairs bar, which was a nice touch. We noted that the table lighting and background lighting was very low, to a point where we had to use the torch on our phone to read the menu, as it was that dark. We were later informed that new lighting was to be installed; but they should really invest in some more candles,...in the short term!! ", "The food was very good with both our dishes served with style and care. The meals were very hot and the black Cod with Jasmine rice lovely, the staff were first class and always very attentive during the entire evening.", "We have dined here previously, and again it was a great evening, despite the lack of candles. We look forward to seeing the new upstairs lighting."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r730307771", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Outstanding", "diner_date": " December 2019", "rating_date": "2 December 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "996deedeed", "reviewer_origin": [], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "123"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "82"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r730307771-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["I was invited by associates for a birthday treat. This was my third visit and each time has been outstanding in terms of food, service and ambience. ", "I've had the seabass twice and it was superb. The chocolate bomb dessert is a must-have. They had the Christmas version with Santa's belt. ", "Prior to dessert, they served me with a mini birthday cupcake with a lit candle. It tasted amazing. ", "I love this place. "]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r730356414", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "4", "title": "Good experience overall", "diner_date": " December 2019", "rating_date": "3 December 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "LambertButler", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "20"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "4"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r730356414-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Had a nice family meal at The Ivy in Canary Wharf. The restaurant has the usual nice decor. Great place to take your family (more suited to adults I\u2019d say) and friends, lovers. Food was good. Lobster risotto was delicious and for \u00a314 well worth it. ", "The service timing was hit and miss and they weren\u2019t that busy. It didn\u2019t bother me but definitely something they can improve. I\u2019d go back as I like the chain and food in general. They also brought me out a mini cake as it was my birthday. :)"]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r729748423", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "2", "title": "Disappointing ", "diner_date": " November 2019", "rating_date": "30 November 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "415stuartf", "reviewer_origin": [], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "2"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "3"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r729748423-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Expected great things from the Ivy - sadly was underwhelmed and will not be returning.", "We arrived for a table of 9 for breakfast. ", "Pros:", "Nice venue", "Opulent decor", "Cons;", "Coffees lukewarm at best", "Some breakfast orders incorrect", "One full English arrived with Mushroom , which was explicitly not asked for, the waiter took the plate back and returned with the same breakfast with the scrape marks on the plate where the mushroom had once been.", "Sadly for high end eatery you would expect more. ", "But the most disturbing feature was the complete lack of engagement from the staff. "]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r731228674", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "2", "title": "Overpriced ", "diner_date": " December 2019", "rating_date": "7 December 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "arsenal7533", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "167"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "90"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r731228674-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["I had lunch with a friend at The Ivy. The restaurant offers a great atmosphere and staff is very friendly and nice. However food is disappointing and over priced. I ordered a \u00ab\u00a0half roasted chicken\u00a0\u00bb at \u00a317.5. It was actually a medium size chicken breast which sold for \u00a38.25 at Nando\u2019s . Total rip off. "]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r730586422", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "4", "title": "Didn't meet my expectations - breakfast", "diner_date": " December 2019", "rating_date": "4 December 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "streetfighter65", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "103"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "27"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["20", "30", "40"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r730586422-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["The aesthetics of the place is clearly its selling point: a beautiful dining room clearly designed with excellent attention to detail. ", "We made a reservation for breakfast, however we were delayed by public transport and called to say we'd be there before 11:30 (when breakfast ended). They told me it was no problem and turned up at 11:25. I had to specifically ask for the breakfast menu - which I understand - and asked if we were still in time for breakfast, something our server had to double-check. I knew it was pushing it a little bit (11:27), but reassured them we knew it was late and we would be very quick in ordering.", "A manager then came to us asking what the problem was, although how this became a big problem is still unknown to me (something our server later kindly apologised for). We had to explain that we had been delayed and wished to have breakfast there. He then asked us if we had booked for breakfast and said \u201cdo you know already what you want to order?\u201d, which made us feel unwelcome and rushed, considering it was our first time and had still not been given the menu. After an uncalled joke, he then gave us the menu and we quickly picked our items, while the waitress was standing in front of us (11:31 was in fact the time printed on the bill).", "Our hot drinks came quickly (though one of them was a hot very sweet white chocolate, instead of a standard hot chocolate) and a while after came the food. I did not want to complain about the mistake and kept my chocolate as it was. Coffee was good, but not remarkable.", "The pancakes were also good, although the strawberries tasted funny and the yogurt made them a little floppy and not easy to swallow. The eggs were nice and so was the croissant. At one point we were asked if we wanted to water and were given a still bottle, without being asked if we preferred sparkling. Surely not the end of the world, but I would expect that in a fine-dining restaurant.", "The very lovely and unexpected touch was when we were given a birthday treat with a candle on, which we very much appreciated. Our server Stephanie was also kind enough to offer to take a picture for us. ", "To sum up: ", "the place looks stunning and refined. The service could use some fine tuning, though as I said Stephanie B. was very nice and quickly made up for the initial slip. Breakfast food is okay, it was good but neither of us were mind-blown. ", "We don't look forward to going back very soon, but may give it another go in the future, hoping that we will be treated a bit better."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r732256384", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Dinner before Michael Buble", "diner_date": " December 2019", "rating_date": "12 December 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Carole w", "reviewer_origin": ["Newcastle upon Tyne, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "39"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "15"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r732256384-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Fantastic atmosphere, first class staff, but the star of the show was the food , absolutely delicious. We both had the same starter, mushrooms, with potato rosti, then I had fish & chips, my son chose chicken Milanese. We loved everything."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r730863608", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "4", "title": "Fab food, great views, loved it", "diner_date": " December 2019", "rating_date": "5 December 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "paulyb3000", "reviewer_origin": ["Brighton, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "813"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "267"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["40", "40", "40"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r730863608-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["The standard Ivy menu never fails to deliver and combined with solid service, it's always a winning combination and manages to feel decadent and special every time. Duck salad, Halloumi open sandwich, thick cut chips and the best creme brulee I've ever eaten (perfect creme anglaise custard and the thinnest and crispest of brulee toppings). A lovely way to spend a couple of hours over lunch."]}
