{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r716324164", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "4", "title": "Luncheon", "diner_date": " October 2019", "rating_date": "8 October 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "annsypansy49", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "81"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "69"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["30", "40", "40"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r716324164-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Came for Brunch and were greeted warmly by the staff. We had a nice table and the atmosphere was good. Had the special from the menu which was nice too. A couple of things that niggled however, having a bottle of wine between three people which was topped up into our glasses (to almost the top) without/or before being asked if we would like more and hence we were asked three times would we like \"another bottle\" having already said no the first time we were asked. Ketchup chilled to the point of freezing cold in a small glass dish that overflowed onto the table as it was so full, this did not compliment the chips at all as it was devoid of taste being so cold. Would I visit again probably not as it is quite pricey and \"good\" not \"excellent\"."]}
