{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r721782021", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "3", "title": "Not up to expectation", "diner_date": " October 2019", "rating_date": "27 October 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "pauljjj2017", "reviewer_origin": ["Maidstone, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "76"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "21"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r721782021-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["I had really high expectations due to the menu check on web site. Went with my wife late afternoon on Saturday. The venue looked positive and the staff were professional from the door to table. Both of us went for the al la carte menus. I will speak for myself, I went for an expensive starter of seafood in Marie Rose sauce, at about \u00a314 I thought this would exceptional, it wasn\u2019t. Something didn\u2019t taste right and I think it was the avacado. Onwards, I went for the rib eye on the bone, \u00a332 excluding sauce. I found it undercooked and very fatty. I didn\u2019t enjoy it. I did point this out to the the waitress who to be fair did remove the cost of my soft drink and glass of wine from the bill. As a point of note when a customer points out how fatty the piece of meat is don\u2019t try and tell me that\u2019s to enhance the cooking! This was one of the most expensive items on the menu and if such should be exceptional. I was really looking forward to this meal and felt let down. won\u2019t go again."]}
