{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r700173115", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Beautiful family brunch", "diner_date": " August 2019", "rating_date": "18 August 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Meg R", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "1"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["50", "50", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r700173115-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Gorgeous restaurant with so many beautiful corners, garden, ground floor and romantic first floor. We felt so welcomed by staff and reception team, who accommodated us with 2 crazy kids. Staff were so attentive, explained kids dishes before we asked also provided colouring paper. Food delicious with so many options and brunch dishes. Definitely we will return."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r700632253", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "3", "title": "Disappointing champagne afternoon tea", "diner_date": " August 2019", "rating_date": "19 August 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Leena1985", "reviewer_origin": ["Ilford, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "142"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "46"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["30", "30", "30"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r700632253-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Firstly, the atmosphere at the Ivy is amazing. The setting of the tables are perfect and everything is laid out beautifully. I came for afternoon tea with friends and decided on the Champagne afternoon tea. We waited a while to be served and we asked for our hot drinks to be served a little after our champagne as we wanted to finish our champagne first. We got served our champagne and very soon after we received our tea which got cold by the time we finished our Champagne. I ordered an Earl Grey tea and it tasted disgusting. It would happen to be the first time I have ordered an Earl Grey tea and been disappointed. I then ordered a latte and it was cold. We were given 3 finger sandwiches and 3 mini desserts and two scones each. The scones had raisins in them which were disappointing, it would've been nice to have a plain one."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r700618857", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Three visits to the Ivy", "diner_date": " August 2019", "rating_date": "19 August 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Salina85b", "reviewer_origin": [], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "40"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "12"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r700618857-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["I wanted to wait to make sure I\u2019d given this restaurant a fair chance before leaving a review - so this is the comparison of three visits. ", "On my first visit the service was lacking but the food and venue were lovely. Service was removed from the bill as we had been left pretty much to our own devices all evening and had to ask every time we needed something - including to order. From this occasion the Ivy took on board our feedback and thanked the group for being honest. The manager told me they wanted constructive feedback to learn and ensure a good customer experience. ", "I\u2019ve dined twice with the Ivy since. And I can say that the service was honestly top notch - the staff didn\u2019t remember us so I believe the service was not to play up for a previous poor experience. ", "The second dining experience was with the same group of friends for dinner and the third occasion for afternoon tea with a relative. On both occasions the service was wonderful. The staff were very friendly and ensured that we had everything we needed. They took the time to help make selections of food and drinks and generally ensured that we enjoyed our dining experience. ", "The hostess took time to show me tables in the restaurant for afternoon tea and asked me to pick the one I liked most. That table was then booked for me. During the afternoon tea the staff spoke to us and returned to the table to check on us and top up our tea very. It and then. They were all very polite and professional. The afternoon tea was wonderful and we enjoyed the afternoon at a leisurely pace. ", "It seemed to me that the Ivy has given itself high standards of service and are working to ensure that high standards are maintained. They were genuinely disappointed that the service was not the \u2018Ivy\u2019 standard during our first experience but I believe that was the exception and not the norm. Both experiences afterwards were flawless. ", "The food and drinks are beautifully presented and tasty. The venue is simply stunning - set on the green at Canary Wharf, with outside and indoor options. You might expect that dinning would be very expensive but it is surprisingly affordable - I was pleasantly surprised. ", "The staff are welcoming and service is swift. I\u2019d recommend this venue and will dine again soon. "]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r703251989", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Second visit spotless ", "diner_date": " August 2019", "rating_date": "26 August 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "martinadaniele", "reviewer_origin": [], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "4"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "3"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r703251989-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["My last visit was a bit disappointing but the food was good so I decided to book again and try the brunch. I always gave a second chance cause I understand that sometimes can be a bad day for everyone specially for the servers. ", "In that case was more than a surprise for me. Service perfect, food amazing, everything quick and tasty... the best eggs royals ever. I will came back 100% "]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r704470272", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Brilliant food and service! ", "diner_date": " August 2019", "rating_date": "30 August 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "jdpecholt", "reviewer_origin": ["Billericay, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "17"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "3"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r704470272-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["I went to the Ivy last night with a friend who was visiting from Australia and we had the most wonderful time. The service was flawless and the food was spectacular! I can only highly recommended visiting the Ivy at canary wharf, you don't be dissapointed. "]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r705039549", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "2", "title": "UNDER PRESSURE", "diner_date": " August 2019", "rating_date": "31 August 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "E3475RBmartinab", "reviewer_origin": [], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "2"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "3"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r705039549-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["2 stars just because of the cocktails and the Tarte Tatin (delicious). The poorest customer service ever experienced in my life.", "-very good in how to make somebody feel uncomfortable, I mean guys...Do you know what a smile is? ", "-if I am still drinking my cocktail, why do you think I have finished with that? UNDER PRESSURE. ", "- unfortunately we didn\u2019t ask for the bill, and it has been given to us, rudely by the unfriendly Alin (Do you know darling you have to look people in the eyes? Specially if you bring the bill... Not requested).", "-oh yes, the 12,5%.... really? Which service? ", "-anyway shame, we really wanted to drink another one, but the frustration of the whole service made us leave (run baby run!)", "- end of the story? If you want a cocktail, they are very nice, so better if you seat on the bar stools, the bartenders seemed nice and more professional. "]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r693642698", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "4", "title": "Food Great, Location Great, Service Not So Great.", "diner_date": " June 2019", "rating_date": "29 July 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "30statesJo", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "495"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "203"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["40", "30", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r693642698-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["We ventured in to the Ivy at Canary Wharf on a Sunday when it was a little more relaxed and less business-lunch-y. The d\u00e9cor is lovely \u2013 over the top quirky/opulent. We were seated downstairs on a table for two, where we had a nice view of both the restaurant and the conservatory. The restaurant was fairly busy \u2013 lots of couples taking a late lunch, tourists, families \u2013 but not packed. ", "Foodwise, I ordered a mocktail and olives to start, shepherd\u2019s pie and a rhumbaba for dessert. All the food was very good, but dessert was the standout dish for me. It wasn\u2019t like the dense syrupy-circles of sponge topped with a swirl of faux-cream that I loved way back in the kebab houses of my youth. Oh no. This was the real deal \u2013 as light as a feather, served with rich, rummy, pouring syrup (I\u2019m smiling at the memory). ", "The disappointment here was the service. There were lots of waiters around, but never at the right time. No less than three people tried to take our drink orders, our olive momentarily visited another table and trying to make eye contact with anyone to get the bill became a bit of game. ", "So, go for the food, go for the people watching but don\u2019t go in a hurry!"]}
