{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r658178643", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "3", "title": "if you don't dress the part, expect poor service", "diner_date": " February 2019", "rating_date": "13 March 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "honestyinreviews", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "18"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "5"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["30", "20", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r658178643-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["I have been to this restaurant a number of times and I have to say the food is excellent every time. The only downside is that you will get treated according to your looks. whenever I have been smartly dressed, I have received excellent service. the last time I went I was disappointed to be given a table with a terrible view of construction and the worst service. I had to wait for ages to be served for my order and my food was not delivered as it was meant to. my bread came with my main meal and they forgot one item I ordered. hopefully this was an oversight but I doubt it very much. I will try again and amend the review the next time I go in jeans and trainers!"]}
