{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r653171182", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Always outstanding", "diner_date": " February 2019", "rating_date": "18 February 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Fredericka F", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "10"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "4"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["50", "50", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r653171182-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Myself and my partner are frequent visitors here, whether it's for Valentines Day or for date night, The Ivy continuously offers wonderful food and great wine in a beautiful setting. The wait staff are always incredibly attentive and friendly even on the busiest of nights. ", "The prices aren't extortionate and the experience as a whole is perfect!"]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r653186499", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "January Date Night", "diner_date": " January 2019", "rating_date": "18 February 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "MSsHoliday", "reviewer_origin": ["Ilford, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "56"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "31"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["50", "50", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r653186499-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["So my partner and I have decided to go to one michelin restaurant per month.", "We started off with Canary Wharf The Ivy in the Park - and what a way to start our michelin restaurant journey.", "We were very impressed with our waiter (did not get his name - he was young black man with glasses) he knew everything about the restaurant, the food and drinks, he was very helpful. ", "We went on Sunday evening so it wasn't very busy but I can imagine the restaurant being very busy at times. I am glad we came on a Sunday evening so we enjoyed the evening peacefully.", "The food was lovely and everything I would expect from a michelin restaurant.", "We ordered; ", "Starters; Lobster and Prawn cocktail - this was alot larger than I had expected and made me feel very full. Crispy duck salad - this was a little smaller than I had expect and I would have liked more duck in the salad however the duck was so lovely and the sauce with the salad gave it a sweet taste which went perfectly.", "Mains: Fillet 7oz steak with truffle and Parmesan chips and peppercorn sauce, my partner asked for medium to well done steak and it was cooked perfectly and the peppercorn sauce was nice and smoothly. However he was not a fan of the truffle and Parmesan chips - he said it was slightly on oil side and the parmesan had a strangle smell. I ordered Chicken bourguignon - this was amazing, the egg on top of the chicken was perfect and when I cut the egg, the yolk run on to the chicken perfectly, I also ordered the truffle parmesan chips and I absolutely loved them. 10/10", "Dessert: My partner ordered Cappuccino cake with he ate without saying a word so he really enjoyed, and I ordered chocolate bombe however they did not have it available so I ordered chocolate truffle which were amazing, the chocolate in the middle was perfectly temperature and melted nicely.", "Drinks: Ivy special G&T - this is a must!!! this is one of the best drinks I have ever ordered!!! and a Canda goose cosmopolitan which was nice.", "Ivy in the park is excellent and I will definitely be going here alot!!!"]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r652943392", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Dinner for 60th birthday celebration", "diner_date": " February 2019", "rating_date": "17 February 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "708keithb", "reviewer_origin": ["Great Leighs, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "76"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "32"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["10", "10", "30"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r652943392-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["We were six people with a table at 8.30 pm.. the name of the table was under Caward ", "First of all we were sat upstairs besides a work station.. not a great start . ", "We were being served by a young lady who only started on Monday ( not her fault ) . But she was not very confident . We asked what the specials were and she told us without any explanation of their content or how they were cooked. My wife and two others then asked for tempura prawns as a starter to be told there were no tempura prawns, sirloin steak was also unavailable . How can that happen on a busy Saturday night in a high class establishment.. ", "we all had our starters which were nice, and then were told that two of the main courses we ordered (lobster linguine ) were now no longer available . Extraordinary! ", "I asked to speak with a manager and after a small discussion going on in the background between what seemed to be a number off managers, a very confident manger arrived and said that we were now going to be personally looked after by him and he then proceeded to sell us the idea that the chef will do us a special linguine with crab .. the girls agreed to have that. ", "We were then left to our own devices and had empty glasses. I had to get up and personally find our white wine and pour it out for the table .. incredible. The mains arrived, and the crab linguine was average at best ( pasta very sticky ) . I had fish and chips and had an extra portion of mushy peas because I wasn\u2019t told mushy peas came with the dish.. ", "My wife then went to the toilet and found there were no hand towels at all, to dry her hands.", "All in all the evening was not what we expected. I eat at The Ivy Liverpool Street frequently with clients and friends, and it is so so much better . ", "When were ordered our last drinks I made the waitress aware of our terrible evening and a lovely manager ( Gloria ) came and listened to my moans and immediately went off and came back with a substantial amount off the bill which was a lovely gesture..", "However as I said to Gloria I would rather have paid the whole amount and enjoyed a wonderful evening, to celebrate our good friend\u2019s 60th birthday, than had an unpleasant one. ", "I would like to thank Gloria as she did her best. ", "The other manager, apart from delivering the main courses did very little.", "We eat out at least 3 times each week and will not rush to drive 1hour 20mins into to the city for average food and poor service to celebrate something special, when we can have a far better locally.", "I appreciate that not everyone has this type of experience but I for one sadly will never go back to the ivy Canary Wharf"]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r651249851", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "4", "title": "Excellent brunch", "diner_date": " February 2019", "rating_date": "10 February 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "TheLoftysPoole", "reviewer_origin": ["Poole, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "632"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "240"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r651249851-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Reading other reviews, I\u2019m surprised as we found the service to be fine. It could have been faster, but overall welcome and attention to deal were good. The ambience is really nice, stylish, warm and comfortable. The husband really enjoyed his pancakes, and the sourdough bread was delicious, I had eggs royale. I like to think I\u2019m a bit of a connoisseur of this dish, and although the eggs were perfectly poached they were a bit mean with the salmon and hollandaise sauce, but I still enjoyed it. Overall it was a lovely Sunday brunch experience. "]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r648324713", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "1", "title": "DISREGARD FOR THE CUSTOMER", "diner_date": " January 2019", "rating_date": "26 January 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "BABAJANGAS", "reviewer_origin": ["Greenwich, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "178"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "127"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["10", "10", "30"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r648324713-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["We were not told that certain dishes were unavailable when ordering so had that initial disappointment, we then ordered what we were told was the last of the dish but subsequently were told that was not available, so had to order again. Then the accompaniments did not arrive until we had finished. I raised this with the manager who said he would give me a coffee and a free meal next time. I waited for the coffee for 15 minutes, it did not arrive and the manager was talking, for an inordinate amount of time to another customer. Literally the most jaw dropping service experience of my life! I followed this up with feedback on their website and have never had a response, this was almost a month ago now..........just woeful. Having eaten at the original Ivy, i cannot help but feel they have overstretched and will end up like many other chains."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r648462351", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "4", "title": "Too dark ", "diner_date": " January 2019", "rating_date": "27 January 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "sawbograham", "reviewer_origin": ["Sawbridgeworth, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "407"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "119"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r648462351-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["I gave this restaurant a 4/5 the food was great but we were visited by 3 members of staff who all just went off and did nothing. There seems to be more chiefs than workers here all who seem a little afraid to do things wrong? Talk about micro management. Back to the food it was well presented and well cooked. Overall very nice. Shame about the service though or I would have marked higher. The soup and the curry were very tasty off the main menu as was the scallops and chicken. Like most restaurants nowadays too expensive for bottled alcohol. The food was well worth the price."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r648596937", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Good find in the hustle and bustle of Canary Wharf", "diner_date": " January 2019", "rating_date": "27 January 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "SmilingTraveller", "reviewer_origin": ["London"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "10"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "18"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["30", "40", "40"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r648596937-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["This is a good find in Canary Wharf, minutes from the tube and DLR station. Great atmosphere, with excellent service and food to match. For the location, the restaurant offers great food at a reasonable price, the drinks, however, are quite expensive.", "The atmosphere in the evening is good, the music perhaps a little too loud and lighting a little too low - I struggled to read my menu in the dim lighting."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r648647268", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "4", "title": "Good food and service but atmos[here a bit lacking", "diner_date": " January 2019", "rating_date": "28 January 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Gricper", "reviewer_origin": ["Fowey, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "251"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "111"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r648647268-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Had dinner here after a movie. The service was good with plenty of attentive people - the food was really good with plenty if choice on the menu. My criticisms would be that the lighting is a bit low and when the place is busy the noise is quite high. Worth a visit though."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r649215149", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "2", "title": "Poor service and understaffed", "diner_date": " January 2019", "rating_date": "30 January 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "galden724", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "27"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "22"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["30", "10", "30"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r649215149-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Let's start with the positives. The vista is impressive; plenty of tall shiny buildings in a cosy and warm environment. Praise also for Mariana, with her warmth and knowledge of the food and wines.", "The downside is this restaurant appears to suffer from one or more of understaffing/training issues/management/owner investment. Maybe this is a sign of things to come due to Brexit and the lack of EU citizens coming to the UK. As the place became moderately busy during the evening, the level of service collapsed.", "We waited 25 minutes for our dessert. When it arrived, the service was uncoordinated and the server appeared agitated. We ordered a dessert consisting of a chocolate hemisphere. A hot sauce is poured on top and the thing melts and is transformed. This works well if firstly you are told to wait for the sauce, then secondly, the sauce is produced soon afterwards. Sadly this did not happen, and my guest smashed into his chocolate without the sauce or the magic.", "My cheese selection arrived almost straight out of the fridge, so lacked flavour. It\u2019s worth mentioning that all of this comes at a price; the Ivy is not cheap.", "Given the concentration of purchasing power among the City people who work in those tall shiny buildings, I have always been puzzled why this area lacks quality restaurants. Sadly, unless this Ivy at Canary Wharf gets it act together, it will remain no better than an expensive high street chain with bad service."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r649025984", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "4", "title": "Nice if you don\u2019t have photo sensitive epilepsy ", "diner_date": " January 2019", "rating_date": "29 January 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "CharlesW636", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "52"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "26"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r649025984-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["We visit most of the Ivy collections. Quite a fan. This one didn\u2019t disappoint. Food great, delivered on time. Reception pleasant. Rich our waiter was super attentive. Manager a little fail. Trying to push Pinot Gris saying it\u2019s just like expensive Pinot Grigio. Nice try! \u201cFail\u201d and then the lights. All of the constantly flickering. We didn\u2019t had desserts, because of slight headache. Still a nice visit hence 4 stars! ", "We would go back only if the lights are fixed and managers gets a little more humble! "]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r650737340", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "3", "title": "Few drinks & meal after work", "diner_date": " February 2019", "rating_date": "7 February 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "7RAC", "reviewer_origin": ["York, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "493"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "427"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r650737340-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Like all recent Ivy brands, not as good as the original. ", "they go heavy on the foliage and the outside area is nice to chill in after work but at \u00a316 for a small glass of Pinot noir it wasn\u2019t welcoming for wine drinkers.", "We were sitting at the bar and even then it was hard to get served at. ", "I ddI enjoy my chicken schnitzel but hard to get wrong. ", "Truffle aroncini starter was lovely as was the trademark frozen berries dessert, but again, hard to get wrong. ", "A good place to go if it\u2019s on expenses. "]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r649525813", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "1", "title": "Another poor Ivy, not a patch on the original", "diner_date": " January 2019", "rating_date": "1 February 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Barry B", "reviewer_origin": ["Hoddesdon, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "1227"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "1577"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["10", "10", "10"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r649525813-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Arranged a dinner for three here for this week, we all worked together in the past and enjoy a good meal and a chat, well here we got one of the two!", "Arrived on time for a 5.30 booking shown straight to a table, given menus and the drinks list, we mentioned that we were still waiting on one member of the party so would take our time, despite this we were asked three times if we were ready to order! If only this keeness could remain all evening. In the end we ordered the bread to gain some space.", "When the last member of the party arrived we had to try hard to attract the staff attention to order drinks, when we managed this they took some time to arrive.", "We took the opportunity to order food when the drinks arrived, starters were mozzarella, tempura prawns and scallops. These were reasonable but not outstanding.", "The mains, Shepard\u2019s pie, with mixed green veg, and two specials of halibut with different green veg. All the mains arrived together, but no sides, we asked and were told they were coming. My guests had a caper sauce with the fish, this was stone cold, they asked if this was correct and were told by the waiter that it should be room temperature, it was not even that. We asked for it to warmed, it was but by then they were half way through their fish, and there was still no sides. We asked again, and these we reordered urgently and arrived after another wait. So so poor.", "We decided not to have a sweet, but went for coffee, but cold cappuccino is not nice, so we added the extra hot milk from the white americano.", "The service here is poor, lack of attention to detail. If you like your mains and sides arriving 10/15 minutes apart and cold sauces on fish then this is the place for you, however if you are a normal diner then avoid this place until they can get their act together.", "We asked for the bill and it arrived along with the card machine! I said I would like to look at the bill first and then pay it, staff came back three times in five minutes with the machine - considering they were not busy and it was only 7.45 I can only assume that they were waiting to close up! To add insult to this saga, there was an automatic 12.5% service charge ", "I have now been to 7 different outlets of this group and they are either very good or very bad, with the latter in the majority so I suspect that this will be the last that we try. Thank god for the chat with friends otherwise the evening would have been a complete disaster."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r650144652", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "4", "title": "Good food and great value for money", "diner_date": " February 2019", "rating_date": "4 February 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "RichAndAsh", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "65"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "88"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["50", "40", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r650144652-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["A friend and I went for dinner last week. When we arrived we were warmly welcomed and seated upstairs. Throughout the evening the service was very good and the staff were all attentive, friendly and professional. They went out of their way so that we could have a good evening. ", "The decor was impressive, however the lighting made it difficult to read the menu. We were placed on a table sitting next to each other and would have preferred a table where we could sit opposite each other. Unfortunately, there were no other tables available. ", "The menu is extensive and our food was really good and tasty, they were also big portions. ", "Overall, a good experience and would recommend."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r648169837", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "4", "title": "Very good but", "diner_date": " January 2019", "rating_date": "25 January 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Dave N", "reviewer_origin": ["England"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "265"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "143"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r648169837-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["I must admit the young ladies on reception are very nice and made you feel welcome ", "I took a chance for a table and they fitted us in by the bar which was ok", "The waiters on the other hand need to be more like the reception staff - never felt welcomed by them", "As for the food I\u2019d was really nice the fish cake with the duck egg was the best fish cake I ever had ", "Overall really good and would return but the waiters need to lighten up"]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r647017049", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "4", "title": "Good food", "diner_date": " January 2019", "rating_date": "19 January 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "milanctk", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "69"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "30"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r647017049-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Friday evening (7pm) at the Ivy. Food was really good, from the starter to the main and the dessert. The place was quite crowded, and the staff seemed a bit stressed. Unfortunately, the music was annoyingly loud. Not really my preference to shout all the time in a restaurant. "]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r646645353", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "2", "title": "Needs some work!", "diner_date": " January 2019", "rating_date": "17 January 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "PaulDLon", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "44"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "62"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["20", "20", "20"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r646645353-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Fantastic looking place and a really nice ambiance inside with great views, The Wharf has been missing a good all day higher end brasserie-style restaurant. We turned up at 17:30 without a reservation and was told there was a table until 7. This was fine - our plan was a main and dessert. Drinks and bread came quickly. The order was taken at 17:48 and then no food until 18:45. Fish and Chips were soggy, and the chicken Milanese was not seasoned at all. Had to ask for Ketchup 3 times; finally arrived once we had finished eating. No time for dessert as had to give the table back, other tables around us having the same issue being asked to leave. Clearly, the kitchen was in trouble and front of house needs training, for somewhere that's meant to be higher end than the other options in the wharf I was quite surprised. Having been to the original ivy - the service was just not there. To be fair - at the end, the manager came over without being asked and removed the drinks from our bill. So will put this down to them having a bad day - will come back and try their Saturday Brunch in a few months when things have settled down."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r646381718", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "great atmosphere and food", "diner_date": " January 2019", "rating_date": "16 January 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Robert B", "reviewer_origin": ["Brentwood, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "12"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "6"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["50", "50", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r646381718-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Went with friends for lunch. The waiting staff were excellent and looked after us very well. The food was good quality and the menu was quite varied. The wine was good value too. We booked and glad we did as the restaurant was full for most of the lunch period. Definitely worth a visit and it does not break the bank either."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r647175979", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "2", "title": "Style over substance", "diner_date": " January 2019", "rating_date": "20 January 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Nomad139733", "reviewer_origin": [], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "2"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["20", "50", "20"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r647175979-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Booking made for a birthday celebration, three people, Sunday brunch menu. First impressions of the premises was good, attractive restaurant, in great location to Canary Wharf shops and station. Warmly greeted, but the reception area full of buggies that could have been left elsewhere. Shown to a lovely table upstairs with view of the ice rink. Orders taken promptly by a friendly server. One of our party ordered eggs Benedict, another the pancakes, and the monkfish prawn curry for myself. When the food arrived, initial reaction was that the curry portion was small, minimal prawns and little chunks of monkfish. The monkfish however was tough and could have passed for poorly cooked lamb in texture. The server apologised and took the curry away, after I'd said that should the monkfish be the same in kitchen, to replace it with more prawn. My husband and daughter had of course finished their meals by then, my daughter having enjoyed the Eggs Benedict, and my husband finding the pancakes nondescript. After waiting 15 minutes my meal arrived, served by one of the managers apologising for the problem. To my dismay, noticed that the replacement dish contained only three prawns, the same amount that had been left in the dish originally, ( i would add the prawns were only small , all could have fitted on a dessert spoon, this is being generous) all floating in the curry sauce. Additionally, no thought had been made to replace the side dishes of vegetables which were now stone cold. The Manager asked if he could replace the food, but by then as everyone had finished, i politely refused. He did offer a dessert or a glass of champagne, but again this was declined. When the bill arrived, the curry had been deducted, plus one cup of coffee. I thought this was a miserly gesture, particularly as it had been a celebration meal, poor food and we had not eaten together. I would say that some chocolates and a mini pastry had been left on the table which was acknowledged with thanks. Overall this was not a good dining experience, not one that I would expect from the Ivy chain of cafes."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r646949336", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "4", "title": "Sunday Afternoon", "diner_date": " January 2019", "rating_date": "19 January 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "carl_amore1", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "6"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "1"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r646949336-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["3rd visit to one of the newer Ivy chain restaurants (which are not part of the original Ivy in Covent Garden) ", "Nice atmosphere for a Sunday afternoon, good staff. Lovely cocktails, whilst I wouldn't rate the food as outstanding it was overall a very pleasant visit. "]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r646770273", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Mid-week dining at The Ivy in the Park", "diner_date": " January 2019", "rating_date": "18 January 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "herfavfood", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "21"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "134"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["40", "40", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r646770273-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["The Ivy in the Park - Canary Wharf, London", "Cuisine: Traditional and Modern English", "Style Points: 4/5", "Location: Canary Wharf", "Price: \u00a3\u00a3\u00a3\u00a3", "Overall: 4/5", "A long time fan of the original establishment, it\u2019s safe to say that I was excited to dine at The Ivy in the Park. Located right in the heart of Canary Wharf, the restaurant is only three months young but the expectations are naturally always high with The Ivy.", "Our table was booked for 6.30pm and by the time we arrived the place was already full but we were welcomed with friendly and approachable staff. ", "Food?", "We decided on something like to \u2018nibble\u2019 on first and tried the Truffle Arancini, which were delicate balls of fried Arborio rice fragrant with the lovely aroma of truffle cheese. They were a delight and went really well with our cocktail, the Aviation Illumination, served in a quirky bulb glass to fit the Winter Lights taking place in Canary Wharf during January. ", "For starters, we tried the Crispy Duck Salad and Marinated Yellowfin Tuna. Both starters did no disappoint. The flavours in the Duck Salad were extraordinary and the pairing of juicy watermelon chunks with pieces of warm crispy five-spiced duck was inspired.", "Yellowfin tuna is always a winner but the marinade was excellent and the wasabi mayonnaise really brought the dish together. ", "For mains, I decided to go with the Chicken Bourguignon - flat-ironed chicken with beautifully crispy skin, creamed potato, chestnut mushrooms and bacon lardons. The chicken was incredibly tender and moist and went extremely perfectly with the creamy mushroom and salty bacon lardons. The mash was not too buttery which was good and the whole dish was seasoned perfectly. ", "My guest went for the dish of the day - Game Pie with handmade pastry, baby carrots and baked sweet potato. This was a \u2018proper\u2019 pie with a flaky shortcrust bottom and not just a pastry top. The meat was juicy, tender and there was plenty of filling, whilst the accompaniments to the dish were cooked perfectly. ", "Of course, we saved room for dessert and went with the recommendations of our server - Melting Chocolate Bombe with a honeycomb centre served theatrically of course with hot salted caramel sauce poured on top. With these sorts of desserts, you can be disappointed as sometimes the taste of the Bombe does not live up to the theatre. However, this Bombe did not disappoint. It was every type of adjective you want a chocolate dessert to be associated with - gooey, rich, warming, decadent, oozing, sweet, sticky...I could go on! ", "My guest went with our second recommendation - Apple Tart Fine - freshly made apple tart with vanilla ice cream and again served theatrically with Calvados Flamb\u00e9. The tart was not too sweet and the pastry was crisp and flaky. You can\u2019t go wrong with what is essentially apple pie and vanilla ice cream however, I think the dessert would\u2019ve tasted better without the Calvados Flamb\u00e9, which was a little too strong and overpowering. ", "Price?", "The price is reflective of the name of the establishment and the area of London it is situated in. However, there are some reasonably priced dishes on the menu and you won\u2019t feel short-changed when it comes to portion sizes. ", "Overall? ", "The Ivy in the Park did not disappoint. The food was of a very high quality, the service was great, and it was a fantastic experience overall. Whether you work or live in the area or are just visiting, I would definitely recommend The Ivy in the Park as a place to try some great dishes of high quality."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r648017853", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "1", "title": "Does your face fit? Then go", "diner_date": " January 2019", "rating_date": "24 January 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "elsiezeh", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "5"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "2"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r648017853-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["When a place you're spending money in makes you feel less than welcome, ultimately the excellent food leaves a very bad taste. When 3 tables are seated at exactly the same time yet only the table with 3 black women are rushed out before dessert because they've been there for \"2 hours\", there's only one conclusion one can reach. Such a shame this still occurs in 2019."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r648122823", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "4", "title": "A cosy space after the chill of The Winter Lights!!", "diner_date": " January 2019", "rating_date": "25 January 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "DebbieoPO", "reviewer_origin": [], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "2"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "2"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["40", "50", "40"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r648122823-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["I recently had drinks at The Ivy Canary Wharf during the Winter Lights and I must say it was absolutely delightful. The service was fantastic, really attentive staff, had some nibbles and a desserts to accompany this. From start to finish my guest and I were very impressed. At times there were a few slip ups but these were quickly rectified by our waiter. ", "It is a shame that they seem to be getting a tough time with people insinuating that they are racist. This is simply not true, unfounded and very defamatory to the brand and wonderful team that work there. It is in very poor taste and I can only say that you should go and experience the brilliance the team and restaurant have to offer. ", "Before any one gets offended, I too am a woman of colour who has visited the establishment several times and felt nothing but warmth and kindness from all I engaged with."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r641009415", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Helen D", "diner_date": " December 2018", "rating_date": "22 December 2018", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Helen D", "reviewer_origin": [], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "2"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "1"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r641009415-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Had a lovely time here for lunch, the lobster linguini was tasty and my daughter had the steak sandwich which she said was delicious!", "Beautiful decor and our waitress Hagia was so nice and very professional.", "Can\u2019t wait to visit again!"]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r646365024", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "As Good As The Original", "diner_date": " January 2019", "rating_date": "16 January 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Buns4vs", "reviewer_origin": ["London England"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "66"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "32"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["40", "50", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r646365024-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["My wife and I have now visited the Ivy in the Park on two separate occasions and have found it to be as good as the original location.", "Service was excellent and the staff are fully knowledgable about what is, to all intents and purposes, a standard menu across the chain. The shepherds pie was indeed excellent and just as we have experienced at West Street (the original).", "A lot of effort has gone into making the interior seem as though it is straight from the 1930's and once inside you would not think the place is brand new. Tables are close together, but no more than you would find at West Street.", "The Ivy in the Park is a welcome addition tor restaurants in Canary Wharf and is well worth a visit at the weekends. We booked ahead on the day and found a table so always worth a try - we have put this now on our regular list."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r639719035", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "1", "title": "Ivy Pants not Ivy Park!!! ", "diner_date": " December 2018", "rating_date": "15 December 2018", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Martin S", "reviewer_origin": [], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "10"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "11"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r639719035-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["My fiancee and I went here for our evening meal prior to going out for the evening on a Friday night. We arrived early and we were seated at our table which over looked the ice rink which was delightful! We were pressured to order drinks every few minutes and we weren't given time to look at the menus it was as if they wanted to rush us out yet it was half empty, it was only 5pm! We ordered some drinks and some sourdough bread to share as a starter which was great I must add... However as soon as the waiter picked up the empty bread basket within 10 seconds our mains were on the table and that was no exaggeration!!! How can we be expected to eat a main within seconds of eating our starters. There was zero breathing space between the two courses it was rush rush rush. We both didn't finish our meals as a result of this. I complained to a member of staff whom got his manager. The manager was very apologetic and so rightly so! She did remove our mains from the bill which was good of her but still it doesn't make up for the nice evening that was ruined by forcing us out the door. Ivy Park you lost out on good customers here. We shall not be returning! "]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r639589682", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Excellent!", "diner_date": " November 2018", "rating_date": "14 December 2018", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "SMOOZA", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "246"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "76"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["40", "50", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r639589682-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Lovely decor and great food! Really good that they offer all day dining and you can also have a quick meeting over coffee. Great service too!"]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r647851586", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "One of the best meals I've ever had", "diner_date": " January 2019", "rating_date": "23 January 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Jonathan H", "reviewer_origin": ["New York"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "25"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "11"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["40", "40", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r647851586-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["I went in a group of 6 people. Every appetizer, main course, and dessert was outstanding. Everyone was blown away by the delicious food. Nice views and atmosphere too. Huge, diverse menu. Not cheap but for what you get prices are a good value."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r642127818", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "4", "title": "Lovely weekend brunch", "diner_date": " December 2018", "rating_date": "29 December 2018", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "travellingmama1", "reviewer_origin": ["Bangkok, Thailand"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "92"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "91"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["40", "40", "40"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r642127818-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Went to have brunch here with a couple friend and my 18-year old daughter this December and was very happy with the experience. From the Ivy Royale (a sparkling cocktail that was just impossible to resist) to the Chicken Milanese and the Chocolate Bombe- everything was really good! I also liked the fact that despite it being full, we couldn't hear other people's conversations. Loved the vibe. I have been to many places where you pay for the ambience and nothing else. The Ivy in the Park is not one of those. Will definitely be back on my next trip."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r642549804", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Perfect evening.", "diner_date": " December 2018", "rating_date": "31 December 2018", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "G9398CHsusanh", "reviewer_origin": [], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "24"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "4"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r642549804-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["We ate at The Ivy in the Park the Friday evening before Christmas. The restaurant was beautifully decorated for the festive season. We were welcomed on arrival and given a table in the bar area for pre dinner cocktails. Our dinner table was upstairs where the subtle lighting, huge glass windows and foliage create a magical ambiance. We all enjoyed our meals. I\u2019d personally recommend the Black Cod. Service was very good and we had a relaxed but excellent meal. ", "The restaurant has a great location. A short walk from Canary Wharf station. Definitely one to return to. "]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r644919775", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "4", "title": "Lovely brunch ", "diner_date": " January 2019", "rating_date": "10 January 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "BonBonsBeauty", "reviewer_origin": ["Essex, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "106"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "31"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r644919775-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Weekend brunch was lovely. We was seated straight away. The service was ok. ", "The staff was nice. Maybe because they was busy but the staff kept forgetting little things. ", "We wanted ketchup and mayo: we had to ask another waitress for it. We ordered two chocolate bombs and only was given one.", "Again had to ask the waitress if it\u2019s just the one they given us and she said yes. Had to explain we ordered two! But told them don\u2019t worry we just keep the one! So slightly disappointed in their service! ", "The food was nice but service could\u2019ve been better. Atmosphere and venue was lovely and prices are affordable "]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r641854047", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "4", "title": "Really nice !", "diner_date": " December 2018", "rating_date": "27 December 2018", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "sanou65", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "34"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "1"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r641854047-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["I went with friends for coffee ! Was really nice ! I like their cr\u00e8me br\u00fbl\u00e9e so delicious even chocolate bombe was amazing ", "I definitely recommend it ", "Well done "]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r646094732", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Fabulous!!!!", "diner_date": " January 2019", "rating_date": "15 January 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Escape759631", "reviewer_origin": [], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "10"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "8"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r646094732-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Met up with a group of friends from high school some of them I\u2019ve not seen for more than 30 years. We had a great time. Food was fantastic and the atmosphere was superb. Will definitely be going back."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r645393851", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "4", "title": "Good experience", "diner_date": " December 2018", "rating_date": "12 January 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "SCSLondon", "reviewer_origin": ["London"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "480"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "226"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["30", "40", "40"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r645393851-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["We booked for the Ivy for an early dinner on new year's eve. We wanted to eat at around 8pm but only 7pm was available online. We visited the restaurant earlier in the day to check if there was a later time but there wasn't. As we were getting ready I got a call to say that we could arrive later as there had been cancellations. We were really impressed that they had made the effort to contact us. On arrival we were warmly welcomed and seated upstairs. My seat was on a comfy banquette but my husband told me later that he kept being bumped by people walking past so felt like he was in a corridor. From the menu we selected the truffled orzo pasta and the scallops for starters, which were both good, then tuna loin and shepherds pie for mains with sides of spinach and truffle chips. It turned out that the sides probably weren't needed but we succumbed to the upselling from the waitress. Both main dishes were very good, well cooked and flavoursome. For dessert we shared the passion fruit baked Alaska, which was a nice balance of sweet and tangy. To drink we shared an entry-price bottle of Bordeaux which we enjoyed. Water was topped up regularly. It was a nice atmosphere and service was good apart from the upselling. Overall a very nice meal."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r637698611", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Breakfast ", "diner_date": " November 2018", "rating_date": "5 December 2018", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "jamesbE6333BO", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "40"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "6"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r637698611-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Was proposed the Ivy as it\u2019s new and well I was not disappointed. The place it\u2019s a very comfortable garden room with the elegance of fine dinning with a more relaxed feel. The staff were great and the food was fantastic."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r637036570", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Nice decor and lovely food", "diner_date": " December 2018", "rating_date": "2 December 2018", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "paptan1", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "104"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "46"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r637036570-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["We had Sunday lunch at the Ivy. We were quite excited in having a new restaurant in the area. The decor at Ivy is lovely. It\u2019s colourful and has lots of plants giving a feeling of freshness in the restaurant. We were seated in the top floor and had good views.", "We started with courgette fritters which was lovely and plenty. For starters my wife ordered yellowfin tuna while I ordered crispy duck salad. We loved both of are starters. For mains we both ordered the miso black cod- we love this dish and we\u2019re not disappointed. ", "The service was great and we were well looked after. We will definitely be coming back."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r637156255", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Reliable ", "diner_date": " December 2018", "rating_date": "3 December 2018", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "722sarahb", "reviewer_origin": ["Brighton, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "161"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "64"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r637156255-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["I love the Ivy chain and this one is lovely and quirky and exceptionally clean. We popped in for a quick lunchtime drink and the care and attention taken in making and serving them was a delight.", "Lots of outdoor space with lovely blankets.", "We will definitely return to this one as it really was comfortable and the decor inspiring. "]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r636924125", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "3", "title": "Waiters/waitresses need to be quicker and more on the ball!", "diner_date": " December 2018", "rating_date": "1 December 2018", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Connector47334297063", "reviewer_origin": [], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "1"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r636924125-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["My and 3 of my friends went for dinner. We were excited as it all looked very nice. The decor was beautiful. 2 of us ordered seabass dish, the waiter took our orders all OK. After about 30 minutes of waiting, the waiter came back to say they have run out of seabass. So, then we placed another option. The order came, I ordered the salmon which was nice. Overall, beautiful decor, service poor. Also, be aware the floor is very slippery!"]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r638586993", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "4", "title": "Christmas dinner & cocktails ", "diner_date": " December 2018", "rating_date": "10 December 2018", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "_SBHx", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "68"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "61"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r638586993-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["I have visited pretty much all of the Ivy\u2019s in London, and they\u2019re one of my favourite restaurants. We thought we\u2019d try the new one in Canary Wharf and were excited to do so.", "I have to say, we weren\u2019t disappointed! It\u2019s probably my favourite one. It\u2019s done up so pretty and overlooks the ice rink.", "The bar there was great and the barmen kept us entertained. Walter was a great host and made sure we always had a cocktail (although there was no candy floss for the candy floss cocktail).", "The steak was a bit on the colder side and the chips had to be sent back as they were inedible, the spinach could have done with going back too but we kept it. ", "Because the service had been so good it didn\u2019t ruin our night, and we had a great night - we will definitely return "]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r639414303", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Great addition to Canary wharf", "diner_date": " December 2018", "rating_date": "13 December 2018", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "409rajc", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "44"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "21"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r639414303-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["Love this place. The menu is extensive, the food really good the service is great and the decor is lovely. Reasonably priced too. Will definitely return very soon."]}
