{"id_resto": "g186338-d15238588", "id_comment": "g186338-d15238588-r627210186", "resto": "The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d15238588-Reviews-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "rating": "2", "title": "Poor Service ", "diner_date": " October 2018", "rating_date": "22 October 2018", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "laibonny", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "9"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "7"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d15238588-r627210186-The_Ivy_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html", "content": ["I made my reservation two weeks in advance and I was really looking forward to the new opening of ivy in Canary Wharf with high expectation.", "Unfortunately, I was really disappointed on that day", "1. Poor Service", "A) Got allocated to a tiny table and just under a loud speaker, I could even feel the vibration on my sofa and very noisy. (They offered us another table when we raised issue)", "B) No service for a long time after we were seated. Not sure if they were understaffed ", "C) They served us tea without milk. Did not even bother asking us. Were there any proper staff training? ", "D) We were having afternoon tea but they took away our knife. Am I supposed to use spoon and fork to spread jam on scones?", "2. Food", "Food was fair and okay. Also the clotted cream provided was hard as a stone, perhaps it has been frozen for too long."]}
